Class Counter<T>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractMap<T,Long>
java.util.HashMap<T,Long>
dev.bjdelacruz.katas.codewars.Counter<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of the objects that a Counter instance will store
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<T,Long>
public class Counter<T> extends HashMap<T,Long>
This class is equivalent to the Counter class found in Python. Basically, a Counter will keep track of the count of each object it stores.

    • add

      public <V extends T> Counter<T> add(Counter<V> other)
      Sums the counts of the elements in the given Counter object with the counts of the elements in this Counter object. If the sum is zero or negative, the element will not be included in the new instance that is returned.
      Type Parameters:
      V - The type of the elements in the other Counter object.
      Parameters:
      other - The other Counter object.
      Returns:
      A new Counter instance with the counts summed together.
